  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7103.78 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7115, dealers are currently long gamma and will provide stabilizing flow by selling any rally attempt toward 7115-7150. The thick positive gamma wall at 7200 (+7.58B) acts as a major resistance ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the negative gamma pocket at 7115 creates a magnetizing effect that should pull price higher from current levels. Key inflection points are 7115 (flip line) and 7100 (positive gamma support) - a break below 7100 would shift dealers into accelerating selling mode toward 7110's negative gamma zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to drift up toward 7115 with dealers capping any strength there.",
